Least terns breed during spring on the sandy beaches of North America. Both parents take turns incubating the eggs for around three weeks. Even though they are capable of flying after just a few weeks, hatchlings often stay with their parents for as long as three months.⁣

node.text:
"One of the coolest things about diving is being able to witness up close the symbiotic relationships between different marine species - in this case, between a green moray eel and a small wrasse fish.
Do you know why these two are so friendly? Why/how do they help each other out?"

node.text:
The Bowhead whale, also called Arctic or Greenland whale. 🐋 
Bowheads are the only baleen whales that spend their entire lives in the Arctic seas. They are among the longest-living mammals on earth, reaching over 200 years of age!
Thanks to their layers of fat over half a meter thick and a forehead so powerful that they can pierce up to two feet of ice sheets to breathe, they have conquered some of the harshest conditions in the world. 🐳❄
